g the saturated domain, the rotational distributions broaden (in\ncontradiction with popular models), which we interpret as evidence that the\ntorque must be lower for rapid rotators than for intermediate ones. The cleaned\nrotational sequences from ground-based observations can be as constraining as\nthose obtained from space.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 4 Jan 2021 19:00:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 15 Oct 2021 01:10:55 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-12-08"}
