ion involves extensive use\nof Monte Carlo methods, which is also what the simulated catalogue uses, taking\ninto account as they do the adaptive nature of the mass-peak patch mass\nhierarchy and all non-local complexities associated with the exclusion of\nsmaller haloes overlapping with larger ones: there is no substitute for the\nmass-Peak Patch simulation-based determination of oriented and anisotropic\ncorrelations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 5 Jan 2021 11:09:53 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 30 Mar 2021 15:12:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-05-12"}
